  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Altezza Hotel and Spa is on a half board basis, drinks are not included.</p>
<p>Fuel up for a day on the slopes at the varied breakfast buffet which includes a classic continental offering of <span>breads and pastries, dairy products and regional charcuterie, fresh fruit and hot options including omelettes and crepes made to order.</span></p>
<p>Each evening you can enjoy a buffet style meal with a <span>wide variety of starters, hot dishes and desserts. </span>S<span>how cooking will also allow you to enjoy a dish made on the spot in front of you often including meats and fish.  There are two seatings for dinner, usually at 7pm and 8.45pm - slots can be reserved at reception. </span>On low season dinners can be a la carte. If you choose half-board, your table will automatically be reserved for dinner. You will have to choose the time of your service.</p>
<p>Savoyard specialities (raclette, fondue, pierrade (bbq meats)) are available upon reservation the day before dinner (additional fees apply).</p>
<p>The hotel has a lovely bar with a range of drinks, plus a range of sweet treats and crepes are available, and can be paid for locally. </p>
<p>Christmas and New Year Gala Dinners included.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
